{"title_page": "\u0160iauliai County", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement<!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n|official_name = \u0160iauliai County\n|native_name = \u0160iauli\u0173 apskritis\n|native_name_lang = lt\n|settlement_type = [[Counties of Lithuania|County]]\n|leader_title = \n|leader_name = \n|image_skyline = Siauliai_centras.jpg\n|image_caption = \n|image_map     = Lithuanian-Counties-Siauliai.svg\n|map_caption   = Location of \u0160iauliai County\n|image_shield  = LTU \u0160iauli\u0173 apskritis COA.svg\n|image_flag    = Siauliai County flag.svg\n|coordinates   = \n|subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name = {{LTU}}\n|iso_code = [[ISO 3166-2|LT-SA]]\n|parts_type = [[Municipalities of Lithuania|Municipalities]]\n|parts = \n|p1= [[Akmen\u0117 district municipality]]\n|p2= [[Joni\u0161kis district municipality]]\n|p3= [[Kelm\u0117 district municipality]]\n|p4= [[Pakruojis district municipality]]\n|p5= [[Radvili\u0161kis district municipality]]\n|p6= [[\u0160iauliai city municipality]]\n|p7= [[\u0160iauliai district municipality]]\n|seat_type = [[Administrative centre]]\n|seat = [[\u0160iauliai]]\n|area_total_km2 = 8,540\n|area_note = (13.1% of the area of Lithuania)\n|population_total = 276,406 ([http://osp.stat.gov.lt/pranesimai-spaudai?articleId=1887860])\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|population_as_of = 2016-01-20\n|population_rank = 4th of 10 (10.4% of the population of Lithuania)\n|blank_name             = GDP (nominal)\n|blank_info             = 2017\n|blank1_name            = &nbsp;- Total\n|blank1_info            = \u20ac3.1&nbsp;billion \n|blank2_name            = &nbsp;- Per capita\n|blank2_info            = \u20ac11,500 ([http://osp.stat.gov.lt/statistiniu-rodikliu-analize?id=8446&status=A])\n|blank_name_sec2         = [[Human Development Index|HDI]] (2017)\n|blank_info_sec2         = 0.830<ref name=\"GlobalDataLab\">{{Cite web|url=https://hdi.globaldatalab.org/areadata/shdi/|title=Sub-national HDI - Area Database - Global Data Lab|website=hdi.globaldatalab.org|language=en|access-date=2018-09-13}}</ref><br/>{{color|green|very high}} \u00b7 [[List of Baltic regions by Human Development Index|6th]]\n|timezone = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n|utc_offset = +2\n|timezone_DST = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST = +3\n|website = \n}}\n\n{{Maplink|frame=yes|plain=y|frame-width=325|frame-height=325|zoom=8|frame-lat=55.95|frame-long=23.30|type=shape-inverse|id=Q186410|title=\u0160iauliai County}}\n\n'''\u0160iauliai County''' ({{lang-lt|\u0160iauli\u0173 apskritis}}) is one of ten [[counties of Lithuania|counties]] in [[Lithuania]]. It is in the north of the country, and its [[Capital (political)|capital]] is [[\u0160iauliai]]. On 1 July 2010, the county administration was abolished,<ref>{{cite web|title=D\u0117l apskri\u010di\u0173 vir\u0161inink\u0173 administracij\u0173 likvidavimo|url=http://www3.lrs.lt/pls/inter3/dokpaieska.showdoc_l?p_id=392936|publisher=Seimas of the Republic of Lithuania|accessdate=21 August 2011}}</ref> and since that date, \u0160iauliai County remains as the territorial and statistical unit.\n\n== History ==\nFormation of administrative regions in Lithuania started in the [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania]] in the 18th century.\n\nIn October 1795, [[Catherine II of Russia]] granted \u0160iauliai the city rights and the privilege to become the capital town of the region. Administrative division of [[Russian Empire]] remained unchanged up to the end of [[World War I]]. When the war came to its end, in 1918 Lithuania was restored as an independent state.\n\nOn December 17, 1918, a circular No.1 was issued \"On Municipalities in Lithuania\" that declared that the entire area of Lithuania would be divided into the regions - apskritys (county sometimes translated into English as a provinces or counties). There were 10 apskritys in Lithuania.\n\nIn 1937 Siauliai county's overall territory was 6042&nbsp;km\u00b2 and 210 thousands people lived there. It was the largest apskritis in Lithuania.\n\nIn 1940 the [[Soviet Union]] occupied Lithuania and reformed the administrative system. The county system remained until 1950 when the counties were abolished and entire area was divided into smaller units - districts, or [[raion|rajonas]] in Lithuanian.\n\nOnly in 1994 - four years after the restoration of Lithuania's independence in 1990 - the apskritys were created again. However, the interwar apskritys should not be mixed with current apskritys, as their purpose, sizes, and number are all different, see [[administrative division of Lithuania]]. The entire area of Lithuania is currently divided into 10 larger units - apskritys and smaller districts, consisting of urban and rural [[Elderships of Lithuania|elderships]].\n\n==Municipalities==\nThe County encompasses municipalities of:\n{|\n|-\n|[[File:Naujoji Akmen\u0117 COA.svg|40px]]\n|[[Akmen\u0117 District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Coat_of_arms_of_Joniskis.svg|40px]]\n|[[Joni\u0161kis District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Kelmes-herbas.svg|40px]]\n|[[Kelm\u0117 District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Coat_of_arms_of_Pakruojis_(Lithuania).svg|40px]]\n|[[Pakruojis District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Radvili\u0161kis_Coat_of_Arms.svg|40px]]\n|[[Radvili\u0161kis District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Coat_of_arms_of_\u0160iauliai_Grand_(Lithuania).svg|40px]]\n|[[\u0160iauliai City Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:\u0160iauliai district COA.svg|40px]]\n|[[\u0160iauliai District Municipality]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://regionai.stat.gov.lt/pdf/siauliai%20apskritis_socdemas_11_25.pdf Social and demographic characteristics of \u0160iauliai County]\n*[http://regionai.stat.gov.lt/pdf/siauliu%20apskritis_ekonomika.pdf Economy of \u0160iauliai County]\n*[http://regionai.stat.gov.lt/pdf/Aplinka_Siauliu_aps_EN.pdf Environment of \u0160iauliai County]\n*[http://www.post.lt/en/?id=217 \u0160iauliai Region Main Post Office]\n\n{{Counties of Lithuania}}\n{{Siauliai County}}\n\n{{coord|55|55|55|N|23|18|51|E|source:euwiki_region:LT-SA_type:adm1st|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Siauliai County}}\n[[Category:Counties of Lithuania]]\n[[Category:\u0160iauliai County| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement<!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n|official_name = \u0160iauliai County\n|native_name = \u0160iauli\u0173 apskritis\n|native_name_lang = lt\n|settlement_type = [[Counties of Lithuania|County]]\n|leader_title = \n|leader_name = \n|image_skyline = Siauliai_centras.jpg\n|image_caption = \n|image_map     = Lithuanian-Counties-Siauliai.svg\n|map_caption   = Location of \u0160iauliai County\n|image_shield  = LTU \u0160iauli\u0173 apskritis COA.svg\n|image_flag    = Siauliai County flag.svg\n|coordinates   = \n|subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name = {{LTU}}\n|iso_code = [[ISO 3166-2|LT-SA]]\n|parts_type = [[Municipalities of Lithuania|Municipalities]]\n|parts = \n|p1= [[Akmen\u0117 district municipality]]\n|p2= [[Joni\u0161kis district municipality]]\n|p3= [[Kelm\u0117 district municipality]]\n|p4= [[Pakruojis district municipality]]\n|p5= [[Radvili\u0161kis district municipality]]\n|p6= [[\u0160iauliai city municipality]]\n|p7= [[\u0160iauliai district municipality]]\n|seat_type = [[Administrative centre]]\n|seat = [[\u0160iauliai]]\n|area_total_km2 = 8,540\n|area_note = (13.1% of the area of Lithuania)\n|population_total = 276,406 ([http://osp.stat.gov.lt/pranesimai-spaudai?articleId=1887860])\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|population_as_of = 2016-01-20\n|population_rank = 4th of 10 (10.4% of the population of Lithuania)\n|blank_name             = GDP (nominal)\n|blank_info             = 2017\n|blank1_name            = &nbsp;- Total\n|blank1_info            = \u20ac3.1&nbsp;billion \n|blank2_name            = &nbsp;- Per capita\n|blank2_info            = \u20ac11,500 ([http://osp.stat.gov.lt/statistiniu-rodikliu-analize?id=8446&status=A])\n|blank_name_sec2         = [[Human Development Index|HDI]] (2017)\n|blank_info_sec2         = 0.830<ref name=\"GlobalDataLab\">{{Cite web|url=https://hdi.globaldatalab.org/areadata/shdi/|title=Sub-national HDI - Area Database - Global Data Lab|website=hdi.globaldatalab.org|language=en|access-date=2018-09-13}}</ref><br/>{{color|green|very high}} \u00b7 [[List of Baltic regions by Human Development Index|6th]]\n|timezone = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n|utc_offset = +2\n|timezone_DST = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST = +3\n|website = \n}}\n\n{{Maplink|frame=yes|plain=y|frame-width=325|frame-height=325|zoom=8|frame-lat=55.95|frame-long=23.30|type=shape-inverse|id=Q186410|title=\u0160iauliai County}}\n\n'''\u0160iauliai County''' ({{lang-lt|\u0160iauli\u0173 apskritis}}) is one of ten [[counties of Lithuania|counties]] in [[Lithuania]]. It is in the north of the country, and its [[Capital (political)|capital]] is [[\u0160iauliai]]. On 1 July 2010, the county administration was abolished,<ref>{{cite web|title=D\u0117l apskri\u010di\u0173 vir\u0161inink\u0173 administracij\u0173 likvidavimo|url=http://www3.lrs.lt/pls/inter3/dokpaieska.showdoc_l?p_id=392936|publisher=Seimas of the Republic of Lithuania|accessdate=21 August 2011}}</ref> and since that date, \u0160iauliai County remains as the territorial and statistical unit.\n\n== History ==\nFormation of administrative regions in Lithuania started in the [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania]] in the 18th century.\n\nIn October 1795, [[Catherine II of Russia]] granted \u0160iauliai the city rights and the privilege to become the capital town of the region. Administrative division of [[Russian Empire]] remained unchanged up to the end of [[World War I]]. When the war came to its end, in 1918 Lithuania was restored as an independent state.\n\nOn December 17, 1918, a circular No.1 was issued \"On Municipalities in Lithuania\" that declared that the entire area of Lithuania would be divided into the regions - apskritys (county sometimes translated into English as a provinces or counties). There were 10 apskritys in Lithuania.\n\nIn 1937 Siauliai county's overall territory was 6042&nbsp;km\u00b2 and 210 thousands people lived there. It was the largest apskritis in Lithuania.\n\nIn 1940 the [[Soviet Union]] occupied Lithuania and reformed the administrative system. The county system remained until 1950 when the counties were abolished and entire area was divided into smaller units - districts, or [[raion|rajonas]] in Lithuanian.\n\nOnly in 1994 - four years after the restoration of Lithuania's independence in 1990 - the apskritys were created again. However, the interwar apskritys should not be mixed with current apskritys, as their purpose, sizes, and number are all different, see [[administrative division of Lithuania]]. The entire area of Lithuania is currently divided into 10 larger units - apskritys and smaller districts, consisting of urban and rural [[Elderships of Lithuania|elderships]].\n\n==Municipalities==\nThe County encompasses municipalities of:\n{|\n|-\n|[[File:Akmen\u0117_COA.svg|40px]]\n|[[Akmen\u0117 District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Coat_of_arms_of_Joniskis.svg|40px]]\n|[[Joni\u0161kis District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Kelmes-herbas.svg|40px]]\n|[[Kelm\u0117 District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Coat_of_arms_of_Pakruojis_(Lithuania).svg|40px]]\n|[[Pakruojis District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Radvili\u0161kis_Coat_of_Arms.svg|40px]]\n|[[Radvili\u0161kis District Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:Coat_of_arms_of_\u0160iauliai_Grand_(Lithuania).svg|40px]]\n|[[\u0160iauliai City Municipality]]\n|-\n|[[File:\u0160iauliai district COA.svg|40px]]\n|[[\u0160iauliai District Municipality]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://regionai.stat.gov.lt/pdf/siauliai%20apskritis_socdemas_11_25.pdf Social and demographic characteristics of \u0160iauliai County]\n*[http://regionai.stat.gov.lt/pdf/siauliu%20apskritis_ekonomika.pdf Economy of \u0160iauliai County]\n*[http://regionai.stat.gov.lt/pdf/Aplinka_Siauliu_aps_EN.pdf Environment of \u0160iauliai County]\n*[http://www.post.lt/en/?id=217 \u0160iauliai Region Main Post Office]\n\n{{Counties of Lithuania}}\n{{Siauliai County}}\n\n{{coord|55|55|55|N|23|18|51|E|source:euwiki_region:LT-SA_type:adm1st|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Siauliai County}}\n[[Category:Counties of Lithuania]]\n[[Category:\u0160iauliai County| ]]\n", "name_user": "Tekstman", "label": "safe", "comment": "(GR)File renamed:File:Akmen\u0117 COA.svg\u2192File:Naujoji Akmen\u0117 COA.svgCriterion 1(original uploader\u2019s request)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C5%A0iauliai_County"}
{"title_page": "Monetary Policy Committee (India)", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox government agency\n| name = Monetary Policy Committee\n| seal = \n| logo = \n| formed = \n| jurisdiction = \n| employees = \n| budget = \n| chief1_name = [[Shaktikanta Das]], [[Indian Administrative Service|IAS]]\n| chief1_position = [[Governor of the Reserve Bank of India]] and ''ex-officio'' chairperson\n| chief2_name = \n| chief2_position = \n| chief3_name = \n| chief3_position = \n| chief4_name = \n| chief4_position = \n| chief5_name = \n| chief5_position = \n| chief6_name = \n| chief6_position = \n| chief7_name = \n| chief7_position = \n| chief8_name = \n| chief8_position = \n| chief9_name = \n| chief9_position = \n| parent_department = [[Reserve Bank of India]]\n| parent_agency =\n| website = \n| type = Committee\n}}\n\nThe '''Monetary Policy Committee''' is responsible for fixing the benchmark [[interest rate]] in [[India]]. The meetings of the Monetary Policy Committee are held at least 4 times a year and it publishes its decisions after each such meeting.\n\nThe committee comprises six members - three officials of the [[Reserve Bank of India]] and three external members nominated by the [[Government of India]]. They need to observe a \"silent period\" seven days before and after the rate decision for \"utmost confidentiality\".  The [[Governor of Reserve Bank of India]] is the chairperson [[Ex officio member|ex officio]] of the committee. Decisions are taken by majority with the Governor having the casting vote in case of a tie. The current mandate of the committee is to maintain 4% annual [[inflation]] until 31 March 2021 with an upper tolerance of 6% and a lower tolerance of 2%.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=151264|title=Monetary Policy Committee constitution under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 notified.|website=pib.nic.in|access-date=2017-06-24}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934]] was amended by [[Finance Act (India)]], 2016 to constitute MPC which will bring more transparency and accountability in fixing India's Monetary Policy.<ref name=\":1\" /> The monetary policy are published after every meeting with each member explaining his opinions. The committee is answerable to the [[Government of India]] if the inflation exceeds the range prescribed for three consecutive months.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/indicators/india-adopts-inflation-target-of-4-for-next-five-years-under-monetary-policy-framework/articleshow/53564923.cms|title=India adopts inflation target of 4% for next five years under monetary policy framework|last=ET Bureau|date=2016-08-06|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2017-06-24}}</ref>\n\n== Establishment and purpose ==\nKey decisions pertaining to benchmark interest rates used to be taken by the [[Governor of Reserve Bank of India]] alone prior to the establishment of the committee. The Governor of RBI is appointed and can be disqualified by the Government anytime. This led to uncertainty and resulted in friction between the Government and the RBI, especially during the times of low growth and high inflation. Before the constitution of the MPC, a Technical Advisory Committee (TAC) on monetary policy with experts from monetary economics, central banking, financial markets and public finance advised the Reserve Bank on the stance of monetary policy. However, its role was only advisory in nature.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rbi.org.in/scripts/FS_Overview.aspx?fn=2752|title=Reserve Bank of India - Function Wise Monetary|website=www.rbi.org.in|access-date=2019-09-17}}</ref>\n\nThe setting up of a committee to decide on Monetary Policy was first proposed by the [[Urjit Patel]] Committee. The Committee suggested a five-member MPC - three members from the RBI and two nominated by the Government. The Government initially proposed a seven-member committee<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/finance/no-veto-power-for-rbi-governor-in-deciding-interest-rates-says-draft-code-115072400057_1.html|title=No veto power for RBI governor in deciding interest rates, says draft code|last=Reporter|first=B. S.|date=2015-07-24|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2017-06-24}}</ref> - three from the RBI and four nominated by it. Subsequent negotiations led to the current composition of the committee, with the external members having a four-year term.{{fact|date=August 2019}}\n\nThe Reserve Bank\u2019s Monetary Policy Department (MPD) assists the MPC in formulating the monetary policy. Views of key stakeholders in the economy, and analytical work of the Reserve Bank contribute to the process for arriving at the decision on the policy repo rate. The Financial Markets Operations Department (FMOD) operationalises the monetary policy, mainly through day-to-day liquidity management operations. The Financial Markets Committee (FMC) meets daily to review the liquidity conditions so as to ensure that the operating target of monetary policy (weighted average lending rate) is kept close to the policy repo rate. Monetary Policy Committee came into force on 27 June 2016.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://pib.gov.in/newsite/printrelease.aspx?relid=146546|title=Government initiates process to constitute Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934|date=27 June 2016|work=Press Bureau of India|access-date=1 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nSuggestions for setting up a Monetary policy committee is not new and goes back to 2002 when YV Reddy committee proposed to establish a MPC, then Tarapore committee in 2006, Percy Mistry committee in 2007, Raghuram Rajan committee in 2009 and then Urjit Patel Committee in 2013.{{fact|date=August 2019}}\n\n== Composition ==\nThe composition of the current and first monetary policy committee is as follows:<ref name=\":0\" />\n# Governor of the Reserve Bank of India \u2013 Chairperson, ''ex officio -'' [[Shaktikanta Das]]\n# Deputy Governor of the Bank in charge of monetary policy \u2014 [[Michael Patra|Michael Debrata Patra]]<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/newly-appointed-deputy-governor-to-look-after-rbi-s-monetary-policy-division-11579097609165.html|title=Newly appointed deputy governor to look after RBI's monetary policy division|date=2020-01-15|website=[[Livemint]]|publisher=Vivek Khanna|language=en|publication-place=[[Mumbai]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-16|agency=[[Press Trust of India]]}}</ref>\n# Executive director of the Bank in charge of monetary policy \u2014 [[Janak Raj]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/banking/rbi-appoints-ed-janak-raj-as-member-of-mpc/articleshow/73741480.cms|title=RBI appoints ED Janak Raj as member of MPC|date=2020-01-29|work=[[The Economic Times]]|access-date=2020-04-03|url-status=live|agency=[[Press Trust of India]]|publication-place=[[Mumbai]]|issn=0013-0389|oclc=61311680}}</ref>\n# Shri Chetan Ghate, Professor, Indian Statistical Institute (ISI) \u2013 Member;\n# Professor Pami Dua, Director, Delhi School of Economics \u2013 Member;\n# Dr. Ravindra H. Dholakia, Professor, Indian Institute of Management, Ahmedabad - Member\n\nMembers referred to at 4 to 6 above, will hold office for a period of four years from the date of appointment while the other three members are official. All the central government nominees are not eligible to be re-appointed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-business/mpc-members-to-get-rs-15-lakh-per-meet-must-disclose-assets/article19338895.ece|title=MPC members to get Rs. 1.5 lakh per meet, must disclose assets|work=The Hindu|access-date=2017-07-24|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Reserve Bank of India]]\n* [[Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934]]\n\n== References ==\n<references /><br />\n\n[[Category:Reserve Bank of India]]\n[[Category:Monetary policy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox government agency\n| name = Monetary Policy Committee\n| seal = \n| logo = \n| formed = \n| jurisdiction = \n| employees = \n| budget = \n| chief1_name = [[Shaktikanta Das]], [[Indian Administrative Service|IAS]]\n| chief1_position = [[Governor of the Reserve Bank of India]] and ''ex-officio'' chairperson\n| chief2_name = \n| chief2_position = \n| chief3_name = \n| chief3_position = \n| chief4_name = \n| chief4_position = \n| chief5_name = \n| chief5_position = \n| chief6_name = \n| chief6_position = \n| chief7_name = \n| chief7_position = \n| chief8_name = \n| chief8_position = \n| chief9_name = \n| chief9_position = \n| parent_department = \n| parent_agency = [[Reserve Bank of India]]\n| website = \n| agency_type = Committee\n}}\n\nThe '''Monetary Policy Committee''' is responsible for fixing the benchmark [[interest rate]] in [[India]]. The meetings of the Monetary Policy Committee are held at least 4 times a year and it publishes its decisions after each such meeting.\n\nThe committee comprises six members - three officials of the [[Reserve Bank of India]] and three external members nominated by the [[Government of India]]. They need to observe a \"silent period\" seven days before and after the rate decision for \"utmost confidentiality\".  The [[Governor of Reserve Bank of India]] is the chairperson [[Ex officio member|ex officio]] of the committee. Decisions are taken by majority with the Governor having the casting vote in case of a tie. The current mandate of the committee is to maintain 4% annual [[inflation]] until 31 March 2021 with an upper tolerance of 6% and a lower tolerance of 2%.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=151264|title=Monetary Policy Committee constitution under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 notified.|website=pib.nic.in|access-date